ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great course. Provides rigorous training and a toolset with which to analyze problems.
Yes. A good overall real macro course for any person interested in investment and monetary.
You have to take it, so deal with it.
It covers a wide range of topics in macroeconomics, which are very useful for understanding the economy.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It gave me a good set of tools for future research.
Made me to put more interest in macro.
On the whole I expected a lot more out of the first-year core sequence, but Q3/4 of macro exceeded the bar set by the other quarters and sequences.
It is one of my field, so it is helpful for research later.
